  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Tunisia: Legal Environment for Smallholder Farmers&#x2019; Integration in Markets &#x2013; Needs Assessment</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">1) To Identify current national and local legal and governance barriers hindering access to markets for smallholder producers, particularly women and youth, with a focus on access to land and natural resources, contract farming, cooperative work and access to finance, and identify priority areas for IDLO programmatic support. 2) To identify priority areas for IDLO programmatic support and introduce local solutions into the national road map for the sustainable transformation of national value chains, from a rule of law perspective.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Smallholder producers, particularly women and youth</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project aims to explore the legal environment for smallholders&#x2019; access to markets and the value chain in Tunisia.</narrative>
  </description>
